      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the making of chronophotographs, recording motion or change with a still camera of a series of photographic images, either discrete photographs taken sequentially or a single exposure capturing movement, with a blurred effect on the images of the people and objects moved. Not to be confused with "cinematography," which is the photography of people and objects in motion with a motion picture camera.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Método que captura y analiza los movimientos de un obejivo mediante el uso de una cámara fotográfica y de tomas secuénciales. No debe ser confundido con la "cinematografía,” que es la fotografía de la gente y de objetos en el movimiento con una cámara de cine.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor het maken van chronofoto's, waarbij beweging of verandering in een serie fotografische beelden wordt vastgelegd door afzonderlijke foto's na elkaar te nemen of met één lange opname beweging te registreren. De bewegende mensen of voorwerpen op de foto's krijgen een wazig effect. Niet te verwarren met 'cinematografie', waarbij bewegende mensen of voorwerpen worden vastgelegd met behulp van een filmcamera.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refere-se à confecção de cronofotografias, registro de movimento ou mudança com uma câmera estática de uma série de imagens fotográficas, sejam fotos discretas tiradas sequencialmente ou uma única exposição capturando movimento, com efeito borrado nas imagens das pessoas e objetos em movimento. Não deve ser confundido com "cinematografia", que é a fotografia de pessoas e objetos em movimento com uma câmera cinematográfica. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指連續動作照片之製作技術，以靜止不動之相機，記錄動作或變化的一系列攝影圖像，包括連續拍攝的個別照片，也包括在單一曝光中所捕捉到的動作，而移動中的人或物件會在圖像中呈現出模糊的效果。該詞彙與「電影攝影」(cinematography)不同，後者是指以電影用攝影機拍攝移動中的人和物件的影像。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
